result.formatted_address: 5 Hoi Chak St, Quarry Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Farmer’s Cooking

reviews.text:
My favorite restaurant for lunch in Quarry Bay.

The lunch menu has four chooses for the main course, with free flow soup & drink. And priced HKD$68-$80.

The free flow part would be self-service.

They use a local farmer vegetable, fresh & health.

Serving more lady size for their lunch, but you can raise out more rice when place order, no extra fee for this.

Small place, around service for under 30 people.  That would be a fast environmental for lunch with a small space.
They also provide for take away service for your choose. 

Overall, highly recommend you to go have a healthy lunch and get a refreshment to get back work.

A rare gem in quarry bay, they serve fresh vegetables from local farms and cook in a healthy way that brings out the original flavour of the food. Moreover you can refill soup and drink which are again cooked using the seasonal food. Overall you are eating fresh local produce that are found in the season!
Healthy food options at reasonable price. For lunch, free soup and drink are included. The place is a bit crowded with people during lunch hours.

Reasonable portion for female.
Natural taste of food.
No MSG.
Interesting sides e.g. banana, chick peas, etc.
Warm-hearted atmosphere family cooking with fresh ingredients sourced from Hong kong. Highly recommended
